problem_text: m \angle UOW = 50, and OV bisects \angle UOW. What is m \angle VOY?
proof:
Step 1:
Theorem: Known facts
Premises : start
Conclusions: W on AO, BisectsAngle(OV, ∠WOU), ∠YOV, ∠AOC, ∠AOV, ∠AOD, ∠DOW, ∠VOD, ∠VOU, 3.14 = pi, ∠WOD, ∠COD, V on CO, ∠WOV, pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOU, U on DO, ∠COU, ∠AOU

Step 2:
Theorem: Bisects Angle Definition
Premises : BisectsAngle(OV, ∠WOU)
Conclusions: ∠VOU = ∠WOV

Step 3:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠AOC, W on AO
Conclusions: ∠AOC = ∠WOC

Step 4:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : ∠AOV, W on AO
Conclusions: ∠AOV = ∠WOV

Step 5:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : W on AO, ∠AOD
Conclusions: ∠AOD = ∠WOD

Step 6:
Theorem: Straight Angle
Premises : ∠YOV, ∠VOD
Conclusions: pi = ∠VOD + ∠YOV

Step 7:
Theorem: Straight Angle
Premises : ∠YOV, ∠VOU
Conclusions: pi = ∠VOU + ∠YOV

Step 8:
Theorem: Reverse Angle Definition
Premises : ∠WOD
Conclusions: ∠WOD = 2 * pi - ∠DOW

Step 9:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : V on CO, ∠COD
Conclusions: ∠COD = ∠VOD

Step 10:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : V on CO, ∠AOC
Conclusions: ∠AOC = ∠AOV

Step 11:
Theorem: Circumference splited
Premises : ∠VOD, ∠DOW, ∠WOV
Conclusions: 2 * pi = ∠DOW + ∠VOD + ∠WOV

Step 12:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : U on DO, ∠AOD
Conclusions: ∠AOD = ∠AOU

Step 13:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : U on DO, ∠COD
Conclusions: ∠COD = ∠COU

Step 14:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : V on CO, ∠COU
Conclusions: ∠COU = ∠VOU

Step 15:
Theorem: Same Angle
Premises : W on AO, ∠AOU
Conclusions: ∠AOU = ∠WOU

Step 16:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : 3.14 = pi, pi = ∠VOD + ∠YOV
Conclusions: 3.14 = ∠VOD + ∠YOV

Step 17:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOC = ∠AOV, ∠AOC = ∠WOC
Conclusions: ∠AOV = ∠WOC

Step 18:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOD = ∠WOD, ∠AOD = ∠AOU
Conclusions: ∠AOU = ∠WOD

Step 19:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠COD = ∠COU, ∠COD = ∠VOD
Conclusions: ∠COU = ∠VOD

Step 20:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠AOV = ∠WOV, ∠AOV = ∠WOC
Conclusions: ∠WOC = ∠WOV

Step 21:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOU, ∠AOU = ∠WOU, ∠AOU = ∠WOD
Conclusions: pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOD

Step 22:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠WOC = ∠WOV, ∠VOU = ∠WOV
Conclusions: ∠VOU = ∠WOC

Step 23:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : pi * (50 / 180) = ∠WOD, ∠WOD = 2 * pi - ∠DOW
Conclusions: pi * (50 / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠DOW

Step 24:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠COU = ∠VOU, ∠VOU = ∠WOC, ∠COU = ∠VOD
Conclusions: ∠VOD = ∠WOC

Step 25:
Theorem: Transtivity of Equivalence
Premises : ∠WOC = ∠WOV, ∠VOD = ∠WOC
Conclusions: ∠VOD = ∠WOV

Step 26:
Theorem: Solve Linear Equation System
Premises : 2 * pi = ∠DOW + ∠VOD + ∠WOV, ∠VOD = ∠WOV, 3.14 = ∠VOD + ∠YOV, pi = ∠VOU + ∠YOV, pi * (50 / 180) = 2 * pi - ∠DOW, ∠VOU = ∠WOV
Conclusions: 2.71 = ∠YOV
